ibis.cashmere.constellation

Class KernelLaunch

  • java.lang.Object
    • ibis.cashmere.constellation.Launch
      • ibis.cashmere.constellation.KernelLaunch

  • public class KernelLaunch
extends Launch
    Represents one specific launch of a Kernel . While launch methods can only be called once, it is possible to create multiple launches from a Kernel.

        public void launch(int gridX,
                   int gridY,
                   int gridZ,
                   int blockX,

        Launch the Kernel with the specified parameters. The launch will be a synchronous launch.
        Parameters:
        gridX - the size of the grid in the X direction
        gridY - the size of the grid in the Y direction
        gridZ - the size of the grid in the Z direction
        blockX - the size of the block in the X direction
        blockY - the size of the block in the Y direction
        blockZ - the size of the block in the Z direction

      • launch

        public void launch(int gridX,
                   int gridY,
                   int gridZ,
                   int blockX,
                   int blockY,
                   int blockZ,
                   boolean synchronous)
        Launch the Kernel with the specified parameters.
        Parameters:
        gridX - the size of the grid in the X direction
        gridY - the size of the grid in the Y direction
        gridZ - the size of the grid in the Z direction
        blockX - the size of the block in the X direction
        blockY - the size of the block in the Y direction
        blockZ - the size of the block in the Z direction
        synchronous - indicates whether the launch should be synchronous or asynchronous
